  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Bhopal: <a href=\"/tag/dr+krishna+kumar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Dr Krishna Kumar</a>, assistant professor of general surgery at <a href=\"/tag/aiims+bhopal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">AIIMS Bhopal</a>, has been award by <a href=\"/tag/international+association+for+trauma+surgery+and+intensive+care\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">International Association for Trauma Surgery and Intensive Care</a> (IATSIC), according to a press release here on Thursday.The honour was conferred during International Surgical Week (ISW 2026), held as part of the 51st <a href=\"/tag/world+congress+of+the+international+society+of+surgery\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">World Congress of the International Society of Surgery</a> (ISS/SIC) in Mexico City.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>Dr Kumar was recognised for his outstanding contributions to trauma management, emergency surgery, and surgical critical care.With more than seven years of clinical and academic experience, his selection highlights the growing global impact of Indian medical professionals and the excellence being fostered at <a href=\"/tag/aiims+bhopal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">AIIMS Bhopal</a>. At the congress, Dr Kumar joined an international cohort of surgeons, presented his research, and participated in discussions on innovative approaches to improve patient outcomes, particularly in resource-limited settings. tnn                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n   